FBIS3-8694 "dreeu049_k_94005" FBIS-EEU-94-049 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Mar 1994 CROATIA Serbian Forces Attack Lika Defense Lines LD1403105094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 1000 GMT 14 Mar 94 LD1403105094 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] Just after 0600 this morning the Serb aggressor began attacks on the Croatian Army's defense lines on the Lika battlefield, the political department of the Gospic operational area of the Croatian Army reports. The Serb forces opened heavy artillery fire on the residential outskirts of Licko Lesce, and at 1000 the attacks were still in progress, Major Darko Dekovic, the assistant commander of the Gospic operational area said. According to first reports there are no casualties, but damage to residential and industrial facilities is huge. The county information center in Gospic warned the residents to be cautious. The Perusic-Stari Licki Osik-Gospic road is still closed, and traffic is diverted onto the Perusic-Klanac-Gospic road. All school classes have been cancelled until further notice.
